{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/work/2-little-rosebuds/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"2 Little Rosebuds","date":"2020-01-21T00:00:00.000Z","date_pretty":"January 21st, 2020","date_from_now":"6 months ago","last_modified_at":"2020-01-22T15:12:52.000Z","last_modified_at_from_now":"6 months ago","path":"/work/2-little-rosebuds/","author":null,"excerpt":"Creative and site development for 2 Little Rosebuds — a blog all about subscription boxes.","tags":["design","web development"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"aspectRatio":1.7741935483870968,"src":"/static/ab2790e0c90f736bffa60842de98ef88/fc20c/2-little-rosebuds-feature.jpg","srcSet":"/static/ab2790e0c90f736bffa60842de98ef88/6e883/2-little-rosebuds-feature.jpg 275w,\n/static/ab2790e0c90f736bffa60842de98ef88/a09ef/2-little-rosebuds-feature.jpg 550w,\n/static/ab2790e0c90f736bffa60842de98ef88/fc20c/2-little-rosebuds-feature.jpg 1100w,\n/static/ab2790e0c90f736bffa60842de98ef88/236a8/2-little-rosebuds-feature.jpg 1580w","sizes":"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px"},"fixed":{"src":"/static/ab2790e0c90f736bffa60842de98ef88/fc20c/2-little-rosebuds-feature.jpg","height":618,"width":1100}}},"toc":null,"comments":false,"comments_locked":null,"hide_meta":true},"id":"b5dcfb55-0149-57ef-8a15-cce6dca2cf42","html":"<p><a href=\"https://2littlerosebuds.com\"><strong>2 Little Rosebuds</strong></a> is a blog written by my wife Wendy Rose. The site started as a place for her to post about our twin girls and morphed into an outlet for her growing addiction to subscription boxes.</p>\n<p>My responsibilities on the site include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wordpress installation and maintenance.</li>\n<li>Creative, theme design, and development.</li>\n<li>Content management.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"logo-design\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#logo-design\" aria-label=\"logo design permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Logo design</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.63636363636363%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"2 Little Rosebuds logotype\"\n        title=\"2 Little Rosebuds logotype\"\n        data-src=\"/static/6b15f670d8e5ea1550dfcfab89f524a9/bad3f/two-little-rosebuds-logo.png\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/6b15f670d8e5ea1550dfcfab89f524a9/39133/two-little-rosebuds-logo.png 275w,\n/static/6b15f670d8e5ea1550dfcfab89f524a9/50322/two-little-rosebuds-logo.png 550w,\n/static/6b15f670d8e5ea1550dfcfab89f524a9/bad3f/two-little-rosebuds-logo.png 1100w,\n/static/6b15f670d8e5ea1550dfcfab89f524a9/c1b35/two-little-rosebuds-logo.png 1276w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>The <strong>2 Little Rosebuds</strong> word mark has gone through several versions over the years. For this iteration I wanted something feminine — with subtle hints at veganism and “the twins,” to relate back to the blog’s identity and subject matter.</p>\n<h2 id=\"style-tiles\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#style-tiles\" aria-label=\"style tiles permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Style tiles</h2>\n<p>For all my projects I like to start with a quick sketch to help capture the overall tone and feel I’m going for. Creating a set of style tiles in Adobe Photoshop or Illustrator is my preferred way of doing that. Colors, basic typography, image treatments, and any other design elements I’m toying with all end up here.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 780px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 240.36363636363635%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\"\n        alt=\"2 Little Rosebuds identity style tiles\"\n        title=\"2 Little Rosebuds identity style tiles\"\n        data-src=\"/static/1d99a4bf56cf6ca41f2a925a0827b8d4/fc794/2lrb-style-tiles.png\"\n        data-srcset=\"/static/1d99a4bf56cf6ca41f2a925a0827b8d4/39133/2lrb-style-tiles.png 275w,\n/static/1d99a4bf56cf6ca41f2a925a0827b8d4/50322/2lrb-style-tiles.png 550w,\n/static/1d99a4bf56cf6ca41f2a925a0827b8d4/fc794/2lrb-style-tiles.png 780w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h2 id=\"wordpress-layouts\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#wordpress-layouts\" aria-label=\"wordpress layouts permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Wordpress layouts</h2>\n<p>With over 3,500 posts in the last eight years, <strong>2 Little Rosebuds</strong> has become an authority on all things “subscription box.” My main goals were to keep the experience familiar and to simplify the underlying code and design wherever possible.</p>\n<p>This meant keeping the established color palette, but with minor adjustments to maintain adequate contrast for improved accessibility.</p>\n<p>Reducing the amount of typefaces used to improve page loading speeds. And combining the masthead, navigation bar, and search form into a single organism to give space back to what’s important — post content.</p>\n<figure>\n  <div class=\"browser-frame\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 209.8181818181818%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Screenshot of post layout\" title=\"Screenshot of post layout\" data-src=\"/static/6f5ff1ceea94bb973c6fb8103f470f77/eacc7/2lrb-post-layout.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/6f5ff1ceea94bb973c6fb8103f470f77/16841/2lrb-post-layout.jpg 275w,\n/static/6f5ff1ceea94bb973c6fb8103f470f77/50c97/2lrb-post-layout.jpg 550w,\n/static/6f5ff1ceea94bb973c6fb8103f470f77/eacc7/2lrb-post-layout.jpg 1100w,\n/static/6f5ff1ceea94bb973c6fb8103f470f77/a105f/2lrb-post-layout.jpg 1327w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  </div>\n  <figcaption><p>Single post layout.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Post content is given prominence by using a centered single column layout to make reading comfortable. Just Wendy’s words and photographs — no side bar clutter or distracting advertisements.</p>\n<figure>\n  <div class=\"browser-frame\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 104%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Screenshot of category archive layout\" title=\"Screenshot of category archive layout\" data-src=\"/static/20eaff541222d4c768f200558b59acf2/eacc7/2lrb-category-archive-layout.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/20eaff541222d4c768f200558b59acf2/16841/2lrb-category-archive-layout.jpg 275w,\n/static/20eaff541222d4c768f200558b59acf2/50c97/2lrb-category-archive-layout.jpg 550w,\n/static/20eaff541222d4c768f200558b59acf2/eacc7/2lrb-category-archive-layout.jpg 1100w,\n/static/20eaff541222d4c768f200558b59acf2/a2009/2lrb-category-archive-layout.jpg 1388w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  </div>\n  <figcaption><p>Category archive layout.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p>Layouts used for the directory got a refresher to better showcase the 650 subscription boxes listed within. Search, sort controls, box type refinements, and review scores are placed in familiar locations to help discover subscriptions while browsing.</p>\n<figure>\n  <div class=\"browser-frame\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 83.63636363636364%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Screenshot of subscription box directory\" title=\"Screenshot of subscription box directory\" data-src=\"/static/abbc4515f7de52498658830a1866b9c0/eacc7/2lrb-subscription-box-directory.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/abbc4515f7de52498658830a1866b9c0/16841/2lrb-subscription-box-directory.jpg 275w,\n/static/abbc4515f7de52498658830a1866b9c0/50c97/2lrb-subscription-box-directory.jpg 550w,\n/static/abbc4515f7de52498658830a1866b9c0/eacc7/2lrb-subscription-box-directory.jpg 1100w,\n/static/abbc4515f7de52498658830a1866b9c0/a2009/2lrb-subscription-box-directory.jpg 1388w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  </div>\n  <figcaption><p>Subscription box directory layout.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<figure>\n  <div class=\"browser-frame\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; background-color: var(--input-background-color); max-width: 1100px;\">\n      <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 122.18181818181819%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image lazyload\" alt=\"Screenshot of subscription box page\" title=\"Screenshot of subscription box page\" data-src=\"/static/d33de04956f254d9ec6fe84e3874dd0c/eacc7/2lrb-subscription-box-layout.jpg\" data-srcset=\"/static/d33de04956f254d9ec6fe84e3874dd0c/16841/2lrb-subscription-box-layout.jpg 275w,\n/static/d33de04956f254d9ec6fe84e3874dd0c/50c97/2lrb-subscription-box-layout.jpg 550w,\n/static/d33de04956f254d9ec6fe84e3874dd0c/eacc7/2lrb-subscription-box-layout.jpg 1100w,\n/static/d33de04956f254d9ec6fe84e3874dd0c/a2009/2lrb-subscription-box-layout.jpg 1388w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1100px) 100vw, 1100px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n    </span>\n  </div>\n  <figcaption><p>Subscription box detail page layout.</p></figcaption>\n</figure>","excerpt":"2 Little Rosebuds is a blog written by my wife Wendy Rose. The site started as a place for her to post about our twin girls and morphed into…","timeToRead":2,"tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/work/2-little-rosebuds/#logo-design\">Logo design</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/work/2-little-rosebuds/#style-tiles\">Style tiles</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/work/2-little-rosebuds/#wordpress-layouts\">Wordpress layouts</a></li>\n</ul>"},"comments":{"edges":[]}},"pageContext":{"next":null,"previous":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/notes/twenty-nineteen/","title":"Twenty Nineteen","categories":["notes"],"tags":["life","web development","video games","open source","Jekyll","Gatsby","beard"]},"fileAbsolutePath":"/home/28041/opensource/github.com/mmistakes/made-mistakes-gatsby/src/posts/notes/twenty-nineteen.md"}}}}